    "handler": "RegisterRequestController.acceptRequest",

    "isPathPrefix": false,
    "isPathLiteral": true,
    "isPathFromConvention": false,
    "isRESTful": true,
    "isTest": false
  }
]

Explanation:
- The file defines a Spring REST controller with four endpoints using @RequestMapping annotations:
  - POST /request/register -> handled by registerRequest(...)
  - POST /request/accept/{id} -> handled by acceptRequest(...)
  - POST /request/reject/{printRequestID} -> handled by rejectRequest(...)
  - GET /requests/pending -> handled by acceptRequest(...) (overloaded method in this class)
- All paths are explicit literal strings, not prefixes, and not derived from naming conventions.
- All handlers are methods within the same source file (RegisterRequestController.java), so inSameSourceFile is true for all.
- All endpoints are RESTful, and none appear to be for testing purposes.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.
